nside a person  but as a complex relationship between society and people who function differently from the norm Disability studies at UIC offers a unique opportunity to study the multilayered  n nRequest info n  n nArrange a visit n  n nApply now n Stats and Facts A detailed look at the program Interdisciplinary Experience Our program is truly an interdisciplinary experience  researchers  and students coming from backgrounds in health  education  assistive technology  medical and social models of disability Your career Students enroll in our program for a variety of reasons and with a variety of goals for when they graduate  disability policy and advocacy  and visual or performing arts  policy analysis Ryan Parrey Munger      Ryan is exploring interactions between people with and without disabilities  n                Meet Ryan n              n                Meet Joe n             Luca Badetti      Luca sees similarities among differences  n                Meet Luca n             Learn from the best Sarah Parker Harris Focusing on comparative and national disability policy and legislation  employment  entrepreneurship and social entrepreneurship  n                Meet Sarah n             Kruti Acharya Research themes include the role of childhood  family and community adversity in the health disparities experienced by individuals with disabilities and the ethics of genetic testing for disability in various contexts   n                Meet Kruti n             Sandy Sufian  Research focusing on the history of disability  childhood and family and the intersections nbetween disability  medicine  and public health  n                Meet Sandy n              n                Meet our faculty n             DHD Connections Our program provides you with the opportunity to embrace interdisciplinary education beyond the classroom and link to the disability community  staff  students  and partners including people with disabilities  family members  organizations  academic departments and universities in Illinois  nationally and internationally Some of our past students have worked in policy positions at legal and government centers in Washington  D C  learning about policy making processes that affect the lives of disabled citizens and their families  Others have traveled internationally to conduct research  present papers  and participate in service initiatives as they learn how the disability studies knowledge base can expand to incorporate experiences of disability in many cultures Drew Egli visits the Wolfensberger Archives  the Munroe Meyer Institute  and the UNMC library  n                    Learn more about Drew s experience  n                  n nAssociation of University Centers on Disabilities Trainee Network n nWhen you become a part of the Department of Disability and Human Development based interdisciplinary programs n n n Association of University Centers on Disabilities Trainee Network When you become a part of the Department of Disability and Human Development based interdisciplinary programs  n nDHD Research Centers  Clinical and Community Programs n nWe are committed to integrating research and academics with community engagement n n n DHD Research Centers  Clinical and Community Programs We are committed to integrating research and academics with community engagement  n nDHD Community Partners n nDHD s work is informed and facilitated by a collaborative network n n n DHD Community Partners DHD s work is informed and facilitated by a collaborative network We re here for you dhdosa uic edu dhdosa uic edu                                West Roosevelt Road r n    DHSP  MC      r nChicago  IL            n Disability and Human Development Disability and Human Development  n nBack to main content n n n n n n Back to main content Admissions and Programs Minor in Disability and Human Development What to Expect BS in Disability and Human Development What to Expect Before You Apply Applying Transferring from another UIC college 